{
  "stem": "1502.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And the-- they gave immigration certificates to Jews every few months.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "There was a quota of immigration certificates, which were called certificates.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The only job of that committee was to divide the certificates.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's say, Brussels received 20 certificates.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that had to be divided amongst the different political Zionist parties.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's say two went to the religious, two went to the leftist, two went to the liberals, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the purpose of that Palestinian Office, which was a committee.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that Palestinian Office you had in every town in Europe where there was a Jewish community because certificates were coming to every town.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the certificates had to be decided, who is getting the certificates.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So my brother, my older brother, was the delegate of the Mizrahi movement, which was the religious Zionist aided in that Palestinian Office.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, when we went into hiding, of course, there were no more Jewish activities whatsoever, except the Judenrat because everything was against the law.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You were not allowed to have a synagogue, or a-- or a Jewish movement, or Jews get together.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Everything had to be liquidated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was no Jewish activities except the Judenrat, which was controlled by the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So when we were in hiding in the beginning in 1942, maybe it was in September and October, my brother somehow got word that the Palestinian Office is-- has a clandestine meeting somewhere, and that he should come.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's important.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We-- we did not want him to go because we figured that he's exposing himself to danger, and it could be a set up thing.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were many set up things like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then, when people would get together, the Gestapo would break in and take them away.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
